-228 MPA of Bangladesh Navy.jpg|200px|thumb|right|Dornier Do-228 MPA of Bangladesh Navy]]\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Type!!Country!!Class!!Role!!No.!!Status!!Notes \n|-\n| [[AgustaWestland AW109]]\n| {{ITA}}\n| Rotary wing\n| Utility\n| 2\n| \n| <ref name=\"World Air Forces 2017\">{{cite web |url= https://www.flightglobal.com/news/articles/insight-from-flightglobal-world-air-forces-on-the-r-432247/|title = World Air Forces 2017 |publisher= Flightglobal Insight |year= 2017 |accessdate= 27 February 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[AW159|AW159 Wildcat]]\n| {{ITA}}\n| Rotary wing\n| [[Anti-submarine warfare#Modern warfare|ASW]] helicopter \n|\n|2 on order\n| <ref name=\"navaltoday\">{{cite news |url= http://navaltoday.com/2017/09/12/bangladesh-navys-new-dornier-228-multirole-aircraft-will-feature-leonardo-aesa-radars/ |title= Bangladesh Navy\u2019s new Dornier 228 multirole aircraft will feature Leonardo AESA radars |date=12 September 2017 |work= Naval Today }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Dornier Do 228]]\n| {{GER}}\n| Fixed wing turbo-prop\n| [[Maritime patrol aircraft|MPA]]\n| 2\n| 2 more on order with Leonardo's seaspray 5000E [[Active Electronically Scanned Array]] surveillance radar.<ref name=\"navaltoday\"/>\n|<ref name=\"World Air Forces 2017\"/>\n|}\n\n===Munitions===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Name\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Type\n! style=\"width:10%;\"| Range\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Origin\n! style=\"width:25%;\"| Notes\n|-\n| ! style=\"text-align: center;\"|[[Otomat#Submodels|Otomat Mk 2 Block IV]]<ref name=\"SIPRI\">{{cite web |url=http://armstrade.sipri.org/armstrade/page/trade_register.php |title=Trade-Register-1971-2018.rft |website=Stockholm International Peace Research Institute |access-date=2019-04-21}}</ref> || ! style=\"text-align: center;\"|[[Anti-ship missile]] || ! style=\"text-align: center;\"|200&nbsp;km || {{ITA}} ||\n|-\n| ! style=\"text-align: center;\"|[[YJ-83#Confusion between the YJ-82, C-802, and \"C-803\"|C-802A]]<ref name=\"SIP